mildred represents this deep disatisfaction that underlies people n this society. you dont attempt suicide unless you're at the point of despair, tho she doesn't remember clearly at some unconscious level that she's desperate.

something is very very wrong, something we don't see in the time machine. because theres this deep disatisfaction it suggest possibility for change. ofc we also see montg dev this sense first with his encounter with clarice,

she introduces this very inconvenient question, are you happy?
by pg 12 he felt his smile slide away, melt, fold over down on itself like a tallow skin, like the stuff of a fantastic candle blown out, darkness. he was not happy. 

beaty clearly has a couple of functions, clearly acts as his super ego, keeping him in line, but he also acts as a kind of explicator, to explain how tihs society came about, with these extended monologues with beaty. Another diff from the tm where we have a char who undergoes all these hypothesis trying to get it right, here we have someone who delivers the history to montag.

