@feb 11

slave narrative

big issue before it got abolished.
in SC almost 50% of pop were slaves. 

Even with the founding fathers there was some discomfort arond founding a nation that was so economically dependent on slavery.

feeling that american values of justice and humanity is inconsistent with slavery. A concern about "what does it say about us? what is it doing to us? what are our children learning? what kind of a country we are creating?"

theres this dissenting voice that even comes up in the courts, but it just has too much popular support at the time, even to get it inthe constitution.

the civil war occurs and then there's reconstruction. 1865-67, the defeated south & confederacy legally protecting the civil rights of freed men and at the same time you have white democrats slowly coming to power in Southern states, sometimes in paramilitary group led elections that attacked blacks.

One of the odd striking things are the white Dems that first enact the Jim Crow laws to disenfranchise blacks, like creating a min literacy or income level in order to vote, instituting a poll tax.

In Kindred,

Dana is trying to escape to the north.

It becomes an issue with the return of folks from ww2, as institutionalised segregation did not exist in the european theatres. They're kind of shocked to return to these kinds of conditions and demand the right to be treated as full citizens.

Butler - "I dont think Dana could've come back whole from the experience", set in Maryland cos it was plausible.

Narratives - usually written by fugitive then post slaves, enormous influence on african american lit in general. Until the Depression these actual testimony narratives were more common than novels in aa lit. (Look up 'beloved').

Bildungsroman - education, self actualisation

Slave narrative is testimonial. its rhetorical function is much more than just storytelling or entertainment. more to do with remembering or memory oten emphasigin accuracy, legitimacy, authenticity, first hand authentication of these stories was very important. I need this on the record, both for my self and my people, we need to remember and tell what happened.

