  Differential time 
    She can't get used to the routines and rules, to adapt, acclimatize, no space for forgiving, forgetting and moving on
      this is important cos, Dana is so nervours when she realises the extent to which people can get used to exploitation, these enslaved people have become to used to it which she does not experience.
    For her, the trauma is kept very much alive
    More of a wedge is driven between Dana and kevin as a result 

