Cyberspace
  gibson describes the world as a post-geographical world
  "consensual hallucination" - consensus reality
  "it's possible to see Ninsei as a field of data the way the matrix once reminded him of proteins linking to distinguish cell specialities"

  blurring lines between virtual and reality

Simulacrum
  "likeness or similarity" used to describe something bearing

  how is cyberspace diff/similar to the physical cityspaces the chars inhabit?

  what does cyberspace do to the structuring and acquisition of knowledge
    knowledge becomes less about knowing facts or data but the ability to retrieve facts

AI & Simulacrum
  Like cyberspace the AIs are represented only metaphorically, the are only narrated indirectly
    thru the bodies, stories of others

  AI as the ultimate other extreme simulacrum

  Does Gibson succeed in representing AI as the ultimate other?
    what is meant by ultimate other?
      
