@mar 16

necromacer - form of divination where the practitioner seeks to summon some form of spirits for protection or wisdom, coming from the greek for 'dead' and 'divination'
  hence "neuromancer"
    a channeler of these disembodied personalities in the AI

Story vs Plot
  what is the difference between story and plot?
    story is a retelling of events where plot is a chain of events
  whose story is this?
  who is driving the plot?
    wintermute is literally transporting us from space to space to space

Intention
  Tessier-Ashpool goal is conflicted b/w corporation and clan (biz vs family)
  Marie-Frances' goal?
    wanted to create a hybrid entity to look after the best interests of the corporation/family, this thing that ould make its own decisions with the fam's goals in mind
  Wintermute's goal? (pg 269)
    to merge with its brother entity. Is it free to make this decision? Part of its programming?
  What are the goals of the other family members?
    preserve the clan, keep the business going
  Neuromancer's goal?
    wants to preserve the status quo, it doesn't need to merge with wintermute.	
    only neuromancer has any sense of self preservation

Agency
  what is agency in this book?
    how do people make choices? what are they guided by?
    Case - wants to preserve his connection to the net, coerced into making choices
    wintermute manipulates 'givens', rituals of personality, this idea of structures of obsession: (driving bit of their personalities, motivation to go thuru the plot)

  how do characters assert free will in this novel?
    they don't really assert it. few chars are making their own choices

Identity
  "unlike my brother, i create my own personality. personality is my medium"
  pg 259

  what is neuromancer?
    pg 251, 243-4
    sameway a necromancer deals with spirits, neuromancer deals with personality
    a giant construct for recording personalities, and spitting them back out

  what are neuromancer's limits?
    it doesnt appear to have ambition, seems satisfied with itself
  does it have more of an identity than wintermute?
    it might think it does, but perhaps not. 

