@apr1

review
  cognitive dissonnce
    an uncomfortable feeling caused by holding two contradictory ideas simultaneously

  where a character is de-familiarized from their own experiences - what was famliar becomes unfamiliar

  where have we seen cog diss in texts in thecourse?

Freud - The Uncanny
  Definition: an instance of simultaneity where a person/obj is both familiar and foreign at the same time, creating a feeling of strangeness, results in feelings of attraction and revulsion

The Uncanny Valley
  Theory put forth by famous robotist Masahiro Mori: he said that when there are robots cyborgs and other creatures that look and act like humans it causes us to echoing freud respond with revulsion.

  the less a robot looks like a human the more empathy we have for it; at a certain point it becomes too human and famliar and that creates the feeling of revulsion

