  "hand over your flesh. we demand it"

  What are some of the differences b/w bio and mech bodies in the shorts?
    slowly fuse together, symbiosis
  what imagery is used to fuse the two together?
    literal fusing, cables running thru things

Symbols
  the apple
    forbidden fruit - repetition of biblical stories
    a colonizing, as it becomes a mechanical apple at the end
    complete reversal in positions, man becomes submissive to machines, defined by their function
  the brain
    seat of reasoning
    info storage
    what makes us us
      towards the end it becomes an object you can control and create, a machine you can switch on and off and manipulate and move towards a function, a job
  the sky
    a break in continuity
    hope


The Archive
  Jacques Derrida - Archive Fever
    The archive is both historical and natural, ordered and controlled by commencement of events. the archive is both obv tied closely to memory and nomology (philosophy concerned with the laws or principles governing the operation of the mind). Derrida also argues that archives are the place where knowledge and memory pass from the private (the dwelling, the mind) to the public. The arch must then be conservative by its nature.

